#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1417(title) 
msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1419(para) 
msgid "To start the build, type: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake</userinput>\n</screen> (Remember to use <acronym>GNU</acronym><application>make</application>.) The build will take a few minutes depending on your hardware. The last line displayed should be: <screen>\nAll of PostgreSQL is successfully made. Ready to install.\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1432(para) 
msgid "If you want to build everything that can be built, including the documentation (HTML and man pages), and the additional modules (<filename>contrib</filename>), type instead: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake world</userinput>\n</screen> The last line displayed should be: <screen>\nPostgreSQL, contrib and HTML documentation successfully made. Ready to install.\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1447(title) 
msgid "Regression Tests"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1450(primary) 
msgid "regression test"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1453(para) 
msgid "If you want to test the newly built server before you install it, you can run the regression tests at this point. The regression tests are a test suite to verify that <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> runs on your machine in the way the developers expected it to. Type: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake check</userinput>\n</screen> (This won't work as root; do it as an unprivileged user.) <xref linkend=\"regress\"/> contains detailed information about interpreting the test results. You can repeat this test at any later time by issuing the same command."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1471(title) 
msgid "Installing the Files"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1474(para) 
msgid "If you are upgrading an existing system be sure to read <xref linkend=\"upgrading\"/> which has instructions about upgrading a cluster."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1483(para) 
msgid "To install <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> enter: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake install</userinput>\n</screen> This will install files into the directories that were specified in <xref linkend=\"configure\"/>. Make sure that you have appropriate permissions to write into that area. Normally you need to do this step as root. Alternatively, you can create the target directories in advance and arrange for appropriate permissions to be granted."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1496(para) 
msgid "To install the documentation (HTML and man pages), enter: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake install-docs</userinput>\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1503(para) 
msgid "If you built the world above, type instead: <screen>\n<userinput>gmake install-world</userinput>\n</screen> This also installs the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1511(para) 
msgid "You can use <literal>gmake install-strip</literal> instead of <literal>gmake install</literal> to strip the executable files and libraries as they are installed. This will save some space. If you built with debugging support, stripping will effectively remove the debugging support, so it should only be done if debugging is no longer needed. <literal>install-strip</literal> tries to do a reasonable job saving space, but it does not have perfect knowledge of how to strip every unneeded byte from an executable file, so if you want to save all the disk space you possibly can, you will have to do manual work."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1524(para) 
msgid "The standard installation provides all the header files needed for client application development as well as for server-side program development, such as custom functions or data types written in C. (Prior to <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 8.0, a separate <literal>gmake install-all-headers</literal> command was needed for the latter, but this step has been folded into the standard install.)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1534(title) 
msgid "Client-only installation:"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1535(para) 
