#: /tmp/cicero-ivSD/installation.xml:1771(para) 
msgid "In general, <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> can be expected to work on these CPU architectures: x86, x86_64, IA64, PowerPC, PowerPC 64, S/390, S/390x, Sparc, Sparc 64, Alpha, ARM, MIPS, MIPSEL, M68K, and PA-RISC. Code support exists for M32R, NS32K, and VAX, but these architectures are not known to have been tested recently. It is often possible to build on an unsupported CPU type by configuring with <option>--disable-spinlocks</option>, but performance will be poor."
